这都是真的吗？
Is that all true?

1322
02:03:33,950 --> 02:03:35,450
这是真的还是假的？
Is it true or not?

1323
02:03:37,120 --> 02:03:40,410
我们这些失踪的人被指责犯有所有的战争罪
Those of us who disappeared were blamed for all the war crimes

1324
02:03:41,160 --> 02:03:42,700
这是事实
That's the truth

1325
02:03:48,120 --> 02:03:49,620
我受够了
I'm sick of this

1326
02:03:50,410 --> 02:03:53,950
如果我必须保护你 我有权知道你是谁
If I have to protect you, I deserve to know who you are

1327
02:03:54,200 --> 02:03:55,950
你做了什么
and what you've done

1328
02:03:57,080 --> 02:04:01,450
如果你什么都没做 你在那里呆了30年是不正常的
It's not normal that you've been there 30 years if you didn't do anything

1329
02:04:01,700 --> 02:04:04,250
杰米...-不要再从这个开始了
Jaime... - Don't start with this again

1330
02:04:04,540 --> 02:04:07,790
你吓了我一辈子 我受够了
You've been scaring me all my life, I'm done

1331
02:04:08,410 --> 02:04:10,410
我从小就害怕
I've been terrified since I was a kid,

1332
02:04:10,540 --> 02:04:13,370
测量每个手势 看 对每个人撒谎
measuring every gesture, look, lying to everyone,

1333
02:04:13,500 --> 02:04:16,700
说我妈妈是我阿姨 我不认识我爸爸
saying my mother is my aunt and I don't know my father,

1334
02:04:16,830 --> 02:04:20,790
事实上他住在我房子的墙后
when in fact he lived behind a wall in my house,

1335
02:04:21,540 --> 02:04:22,950
像这样躲在那里
hiding there like

1336
02:04:23,000 --> 02:04:25,040
你不觉得羞耻吗？这是我的房子
Aren't you ashamed? This is my house

1337
02:04:26,000 --> 02:04:27,330
你的房子？
Your house?

1338
02:04:27,910 --> 02:04:29,750
什么房子？不在这里
What house? Not here

1339
02:04:30,500 --> 02:04:32,910
那是你的房子 你住在那里
That's your house, you live there

1340
02:04:33,120 --> 02:04:37,620
懦夫躲起来 而其他人在前线战斗并死去
Cowards who hid away while the others fought and died on the front

1341
02:04:37,870 --> 02:04:41,000
在我们继续生活的时候 我不得不躲在墙后
have to live behind a wall while our lives go on

1342
02:04:41,080 --> 02:04:44,500
请小声点 -谁在听？
Lower your voice, please. - Who's listening?

1343
02:04:44,790 --> 02:04:46,750
邻居？-他们能听到你
The neighbors? - They can hear you

1344
02:04:46,870 --> 02:04:49,370
他们从一开始就知道他在那里
They've known he's there from the beginning

1345
02:04:49,540 --> 02:04:51,950
路易莎告诉我她听到他在睡梦中大喊大叫
Luisa told me she hears him shouting in his sleep

1346
02:04:52,000 --> 02:04:54,000
那不是真的 -想象他的梦
That's not true. - Imagine his dreams

1347
02:04:54,080 --> 02:04:58,290
她的父母认为他被关了这么久已经疯了
Her parents think he's gone mad from being locked up so long

1348
02:04:58,450 --> 02:05:00,500
隐藏得像
Hidden like a

1349
02:05:00,660 --> 02:05:02,410
总是谈论战斗
Always talking about fighting

1350
02:05:02,950 --> 02:05:05,700
你的战斗方式毫无意义
Your way of fighting meant nothing

1351
02:05:05,790 --> 02:05:08,410
一个没有勇气出去的懦夫
A coward who doesn't have the balls to go outside

1352
02:05:08,830 --> 02:05:11,160
不要那样和你父亲说话
Don't talk to your father that way

1353
02:05:14,830 --> 02:05:17,910
你不知道我们为你经历了什么
You've no idea what we've gone through for you

1354
02:05:27,910 --> 02:05:30,040
我同情你们两个
I pity you two

1355
02:05:32,120 --> 02:05:35,660
外面没人等着吃你活着
There's no one out there waiting to eat you alive

1356
02:05:37,700 --> 02:05:39,450
我在警察局
I was at the police station

1357
02:05:40,830 --> 02:05:43,450
甚至国民警卫队也不感兴趣
Even the civil guard aren't interested

1358
02:06:04,370 --> 02:06:06,410
伊吉尼奥 -什么？
Higinio. - What?

1359
02:06:07,950 --> 02:06:10,200
你认为这个小伙子是对的吗？
Do you think the lad is right?

1360
02:06:11,410 --> 02:06:12,580
关于什么？
About what?

1361
02:06:13,660 --> 02:06:17,250
如果你出来 什么都不会发生
That if you came out, nothing would happen

1362
02:06:17,950 --> 02:06:18,950
决不
No way

1363
02:06:19,290 --> 02:06:21,080
待在这里是一回事
Being in here is one thing,

1364
02:06:21,160 --> 02:06:23,950
他们让我住在那里是另一回事
them letting me live out there is another

1365
02:06:26,660 --> 02:06:28,580
晚安 -晚安
Good night. - Good night

1366
02:07:03,580 --> 02:07:04,910
谁在那里？
Who's there?

1367
02:07:41,660 --> 02:07:43,660
慢慢地挖掘我 嗯？
Took your time digging me up, huh?

1368
02:07:47,160 --> 02:07:49,700
请把烟咽下去 它有气味
Please swallow the smoke, it smells

1369
02:08:07,500 --> 02:08:08,500
真的很干
It's really dry

1370
02:08:08,950 --> 02:08:11,160
干燥的...你见过自己吗？
Dry... Have you seen yourself?

1371
02:08:11,830 --> 02:08:13,410
你肯定是干的
You sure are dry

1372
02:08:14,790 --> 02:08:15,790
没错
That's true

1373
02:08:19,830 --> 02:08:22,000
你真的很勇敢 伊吉尼奥
You're really brave, Higinio

1374
02:08:23,160 --> 02:08:25,700
勇敢到连自己的生命都不要去拿
Brave enough not even to take your own life

1375
02:08:28,910 --> 02:08:30,580
我想你已经听腻了
I guess you're sick of hearing it,

1376
02:08:30,660 --> 02:08:34,660
但是很少有人会容忍你的正直
but few people would put up with this with your integrity

1377
02:08:37,660 --> 02:08:38,830
谢谢
Thanks

1378
02:08:44,620 --> 02:08:47,750
也许你的恐惧不会让人们把你视为英雄
Maybe your fear won't make people see you as a hero

1379
02:08:49,450 --> 02:08:52,160
但是你也因此成为了受害者
But you're no less a victim because of it

1380
02:09:30,450 --> 02:09:31,870
谢谢
Thanks

1381
02:09:33,000 --> 02:09:34,790
哦 伊吉尼奥
Oh, Higinio

1382
02:09:57,500 --> 02:10:02,950
大赦——对被判犯有政治罪的人的官方赦免
amnesty - official pardon for those convicted of political offences

1383
02:10:46,450 --> 02:10:49,000
这是新闻
Here is the news

1384
02:10:49,120 --> 02:10:52,160
纪念内战结束30周年
Commemorating the 30th anniversary of the end of the Civil War

1385
02:10:52,250 --> 02:10:54,200
以及全国的和平
and peace nationwide,

1386
02:10:54,370 --> 02:10:57,500
部长会议宣布了一项法令
the Council of Ministers has announced a Decree

1387
02:10:57,580 --> 02:11:03,330
下令终止与战争有关的任何事件引起的犯罪
ordering the expiration of offences deriving from any event related to the war

1388
02:11:03,870 --> 02:11:06,950
该法令的序言指出
The preamble of the Decree states that

1389
02:11:07,080 --> 02:11:10,790
这是一场自相残杀的斗争 所有的结果都不起作用
all the consequences of what was a fratricidal struggle, are inoperative

1390
02:11:10,870 --> 02:11:15,200
1939年4月1日之前犯下的所有罪行
All crimes committed prior to 1 April 1939

1391
02:11:15,330 --> 02:11:20,160
将从1969年4月1日起失去时效
will be time-barred as from 1 April 1969

1392
02:11:20,700 --> 02:11:23,540
案件将被驳回并结案
Cases will be dismissed and closed

1393
02:11:23,660 --> 02:11:25,080
罗莎
Rosa

1394
02:11:25,160 --> 02:11:26,870
大赦已经宣布
Amnesty has been declared

1395
02:11:27,410 --> 02:11:28,950
别动
Hold it there

1396
02:11:29,450 --> 02:11:31,120
趴下 趴下
Down, down

1397
02:11:32,950 --> 02:11:35,290
放在床上
Put it on the bed

1398
02:11:41,410 --> 02:11:43,620
不 这是床单
No, this is bed linen

1399
02:11:45,330 --> 02:11:47,830
我们出去的第一件事就是
The first thing we'll do when we go out

1400
02:11:48,000 --> 02:11:51,370
就是给你买新衣服 让你看起来更聪明
is buy you new clothes so you look smart

1401
02:11:52,580 --> 02:11:53,580
让我们看看如何
Let's see how

1402
02:11:55,750 --> 02:11:57,830
它不合适 对吗？
It doesn't fit, right?

1403
02:11:57,950 --> 02:12:00,910
我去拿些剪刀 马上修好
I'll fetch some scissors and fix it right away

1404
02:12:01,660 --> 02:12:04,580
现在把我们的衣服挂在一起并不危险
Now it's not dangerous to hang out our clothes together

1405
02:12:43,080 --> 02:12:44,080
伊吉尼奥
Higinio

1406
02:12:47,080 --> 02:12:49,000
你为什么脱掉裤子？
Why did you take off the trousers?

1407
02:12:52,290 --> 02:12:54,750
我不知道 罗莎 -你什么意思？
I don't know, Rosa. - What do you mean?

1408
02:12:57,080 --> 02:13:01,500
如果一个邻居在追你 马德里人会怎么说并不重要
What they say in Madrid doesn't matter if a neighbor is after you

1409
02:13:01,950 --> 02:13:03,200
什么邻居？
What neighbor?

1410
02:13:03,290 --> 02:13:07,200
你没听到他们在广播和报纸上说什么吗？
Didn't you hear what they're saying on the radio and in the press?

1411
02:13:07,870 --> 02:13:09,700
这里没那么糟
It's not that bad here

1412
02:13:10,120 --> 02:13:11,620
开始
Come on

1413
02:13:14,660 --> 02:13:16,250
好吧 那么
All right, then

1414
02:13:24,500 --> 02:13:25,870
你在做什么?
What are you doing?

1415
02:13:27,160 --> 02:13:28,790
你没看见吗？
Can't you see?

1416
02:13:32,750 --> 02:13:34,250
你要去哪里？
Where are you going?

1417
02:13:34,410 --> 02:13:35,910
我要走了
I'm going

1418
02:13:37,160 --> 02:13:38,330
去海边
to the coast

1419
02:13:39,080 --> 02:13:41,700
去海边 那是我要去的地方
To the seaside, that's where I'm going

1420
02:13:43,540 --> 02:13:45,950
你怎么去那里？
How will you get there?

1421
02:13:47,120 --> 02:13:49,410
住手 -巴士11点出发
Stop that. - The bus leaves at 11

1422
02:13:50,790 --> 02:13:52,500
我为什么知道？
Why do I know that?

1423
02:13:54,580 --> 02:13:57,160
因为我每周都看时间表
Because I look at the timetables every week

1424
02:13:58,290 --> 02:14:00,500
如果你愿意 跟我来
So if you want, come with me

1425
02:14:01,370 --> 02:14:04,120
到了那里我会给你买泳裤
and I'll buy you a swim trunks when we get there

1426
02:14:05,000 --> 02:14:07,200
你知道我不能去
You know I can't go

1427
02:14:07,700 --> 02:14:09,750
别胡说了 罗莎
Stop this nonsense. Rosa!

1428
02:14:12,660 --> 02:14:14,080
罗莎
Rosa!

1429
02:14:15,080 --> 02:14:16,080
拜托 罗莎
Please, Rosa

1430
02:14:16,620 --> 02:14:18,120
不要再离开
Don't leave again

1431
02:14:18,250 --> 02:14:19,250
罗莎
Rosa!

1432
02:16:04,830 --> 02:16:10,290
出去离开一个地方到外面去
to go out to leave a place and go outside

1433
02:18:05,450 --> 02:18:06,750
你好
Hello

1434
02:18:07,700 --> 02:18:08,950
你好
Hello

1435
02:19:11,750 --> 02:19:12,750
罗莎
Rosa

1436
02:19:22,660 --> 02:19:24,540
你没赶上公共汽车吗？
Didn't you catch the bus?

1437
02:19:25,830 --> 02:19:27,160
看起来是这样
Looks that way

1438
02:19:48,080 --> 02:19:49,870
我必须拿到我的身份证
I have to get my ID card

1439
02:20:23,870 --> 02:20:24,870
你好
Hello

1440
02:20:25,370 --> 02:20:26,200
你好
Hello

1441
02:20:26,290 --> 02:20:28,160
我能帮你什么吗？
Can I help you?

1442
02:20:28,750 --> 02:20:33,120
原来我们以前住在这里
It turns out we used to live here

1443
02:20:33,870 --> 02:20:36,500
至少30年前
at least 30 years ago

1444
02:20:37,120 --> 02:20:39,200
嗯 这房子确实是
Well, this house was

1445
02:21:47,910 --> 02:21:53,450
自1969年该法令公布以来 越来越多的案件被揭露 
From the publication of the Decree in 1969, more and more cases were revealed of people

1446
02:21:53,910 --> 02:21:58,450
人们因害怕报复 躲在家里
who, fearing reprisals, went into hiding at home

1447
02:21:59,830 --> 02:22:03,950
这些人被赋予了“鼹鼠”的绰号
These people were given the nickname moles

1448
02:22:04,040 --> 02:22:09,080
在某些情况下 他们躲藏了30多年
In some cases, they remained in hiding for over 30 years


